    "narrative": "The lineup for April 21st is headlined by **Corbin Carroll**, whose 85.94 score represents the ceiling for today\u2019s slate. The matchup against Burke provides a dual-threat opportunity; **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a high-efficiency base projection combined with a favorable 100% SB probability against the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, making him our primary engine for stolen bases. Joining him at the top of the hierarchy are **James Wood** (76.28) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.98). Both benefit immensely from the park factor at their respective venues and soft matchups against pitchers with xERAs north of 5.40, allowing both to exploit their aggressive batting order spots to maximize run production.\n\nTactically, we are leaning into platoon advantages and favorable park dimensions to squeeze value out of the mid-tier options. **Brice Turang** (74.51) and **Trevor Story** (74.11) serve as our most consistent anchors today, with **Brice Turang** specifically capitalizing on a premium lineup spot and **Trevor Story** facing a significant skill deficit in the opposing mound presence of Gil. Conversely, **Jose Caballero** remains a marginal play at 54.17; despite his potential for speed, the daunting 2.34 xERA of Early makes him a high-variance start that we are only keeping active to chase the category scarcity of stolen bases.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Giancarlo Stanton** (48.48) out of the Utility slot in favor of **Vinnie Pasquantino** (65.63). While **Giancarlo Stanton** offers raw power, his score was suppressed by the brutal matchup against Early. **Vinnie Pasquantino** earned the start due to a superior dynamic platoon edge (+14%) and the safety of the #3 spot in the order, which provides more stability for our AVG and RBI targets. We are monitoring **Dalton Rushing** (53.70) closely, as his efficiency is tied to a mid-tier matchup, but he maintains his spot over secondary options like **Gabriel Moreno** or **Luis Campusano** due to the sheer volume of his current usage profile. Proceed with confidence in our top-heavy outfield, but remain cognizant that **Seiya Suzuki** (50.92) is essentially playing for his roster spot today against a tough Luzardo matchup.",
